<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="531">
<specimenCount box="[151,278,1345,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="531" type="male">
<number box="[151,163,1345,1367]" pageId="1" pageNumber="531" value="4.0">4</number>
Male
</specimenCount>
: aedeagus with ventral outline of ventral wall sinuate to tip truncate (
<figureCitation box="[947,1054,1345,1367]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1377,1400]" captionTargetBox="[343,1235,201,1347]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[340,1247,193,1357]" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 22. Megarthrus narendrani sp. n., male; aedeagus in ventral (15, 18) and lateral (16, 17) views; abdominal sternite VIII in ventral view (19); apex of abdominal tergite 8 in dorsal view (22); mesotibia (21); mesofemur and mesotrochanter (22). Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/291814/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="531">figs 16, 17</figureCitation>
). Female: lateral outline of middle portion of valvifers converging (fig. 
<number box="[544,571,1375,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="531" value="23.0">23</number>
); female: genital tergites with two transverse subbasal sclerites (fig. 
<number box="[1227,1252,1375,1397]" pageId="1" pageNumber="531" value="25.0">25</number>
)......................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1137,1363,1404,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Megarthrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narendrani">
<emphasis box="[1137,1363,1404,1426]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="531">Megarthrus narendrani</emphasis>
